<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-917-221  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 917 221.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Sept 13 1989 n1262* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Xerox code enables pictures to transfer unchanged inSystran-slated text. (product announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Xerox Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    XRX.andO;Product:   Viewpoint Machine Translation Interface (Computer program)(product introduction).andO;Topic:     Language TranslationProduct IntroductionSoftware PackagesNew Product.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>XEROX CODE ENABLES PICTURES TO TRANSFER UNCHANGED INandM;SYSTRAN-SLATED TEXTandM;Xerox Corp, Hartford, Connecticut, claims to have the industry's firstmachine translation interface software that enables entire documents to betranslated while retaining charts and graphics in their original form.andP;  Thecapability is significant in the foreign language technology market, Xeroxreckons, because users will no longer have to recreate non-textual matterafter machine translation.andP;  Called the Xerox ViewPoint Machine TranslationInterface, the software was designed primarily for users that work withsubstantial volumes of material to be translated, particularly material thatis technical or repetitive or that has many charts and graphics.andP;  When theXerox interface and the Systran translation software, developed by SystranMachine Translation Systems Inc, are used together, users &quot;can achievetranslation quality with up to 95% accuracy prior to their own editing of thetranslated material&quot;.andP;  The Xerox software provides an interface from Xerox6085 workstations to an IBM-compatible mainframe computer running customisedXerox applications software and Systran translation software.andP;  Currentsoftware capabilities translate English into German, French, Spanish, Italianand Portuguese.andP;  The ViewPoint Machine Translation Interface is availableimmediately in the US for $3,500.andP;  Systems solutions can be tailored to eachcustomer's requirements by the Xerox Custom Systems.andO;</TEXT></DOC>